The paper deals with the recognition problem of well-covered graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The concept of weight functions on vertices and the vector space of weight functions also suggest a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and game theory (cs.GT). The restriction on cycles of length 4, 5, 6, and 7 may indicate a focus on graph algorithms and complexity theory (cs.CC).
